Title: Change Control: ModelShop Workstation & Shared Account Discovery + Profile Integrity Testing
Type: Standard Change
Environment: Production – Engineering Workstations (CAD, Scanning, Modelling)
Owner: Curtis-Davidson
Department: Infrastructure & Endpoint Security


-----------------------

1. Change Purpose

The purpose of this change is to assess and test the transition from **shared user accounts** to **named individual accounts** for the ModelShop engineering team. This includes:

- Discovery of current GPO, login flows, workstation config, and software bindings
- Safely testing script execution and configuration changes on one workstation
- Preserving and migrating profile data (including CAD, CAM, 3D scan drivers, licensing)
- Implementing enterprise-grade methodology for future rollout

Objective:
→ Replace shared logins with properly scoped individual and team-shared accounts, without breaking existing environments or losing profile-integrated software state.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



2. Scope of Change

Applies To:
- 1x selected ModelShop workstation (CAD-configured)
- Current shared account (e.g. MODEL-SHOP\WorkshopUser)
- Audit of tools including: SolidWorks, AutoCAD, MeshLab, proprietary scan drivers

Includes:
- Scripted workstation inspection (AuditWS)
- Analysis of registry, roaming/local profile data
- SID backup, profile redirection
- Backup of current working state

Does NOT Apply To:
- Domain controller modifications (initial scope only reads AD)
- Full GPO enforcement changes — only discovery

Tools Used:
- `AuditWS` discovery modules
- `AuditScripts\workstation-core.ps1`
- `Get-LoggedInUsers`, `Get-UserProfiles`, `Get-UserRightsAssignments`
- Profile integrity script (WIP)


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


3. Change Steps / Methodology

Step 1: Snapshot Current Profile State
---------------------------------------
- Backup full user profile: `C:\Users\WorkshopUser`
- Export NTUSER.DAT, AppData, registry keys via PowerShell
- Use: `robocopy` and `reg export`
- Confirm backup stored to: `\\fileserver\AuditBackups\ModelShop\{timestamp}`

Step 2: Audit and Log Configuration
---------------------------------------
- Run:
  - `workstation-core.ps1`
  - `Get-UserRightsAssignments`
  - `Get-LoggedInUsers`
  - `Export-GPOReport` (target OU)
- Log SID, GPOs, local group membership, mapped drives, CAD registry entries

Step 3: Define Enterprise Account Schema
-----------------------------------------
- Create:
  - `ModelShop-User-{Name}` (individual domain user)
  - `ModelShop-Shared` (group-based workstation access)
  - `ModelShop-G-Workstations` (AD group)
- Configure GPO linking:
  - Folder redirection OFF
  - Roaming profiles disabled
  - Logon script set for logging only

Step 4: Profile Migration Safety Test
-----------------------------------------
- Run test user logon
- Use `User Profile Wizard` or `Profwiz` if applicable (only if profile copy is clean)
- Test mapping profile to old shared account SID (if needed)
- Confirm:
  - Software loads
  - Licensing not invalidated
  - Printers, drives, context menu integrations intact

Step 5: Risk Mitigation Check
-------------------------------
- Log changes to:
  - `HKCU\Software\...`
  - AppData paths
- Run full diff of `C:\Users\OldUser` vs `NewUser`
- Validate file permissions with:
  - `icacls "C:\Users\..." /save perms.txt`

Step 6: Final Report + Rollback Plan
--------------------------------------
- Dump workstation log to:
  `\\fileserver\AuditLogs\ModelShop-Audit-{hostname}.txt`
- Confirm new account performs all workflows
- Rollback by:
  - Re-mapping original profile
  - Restoring NTUSER.DAT and folder backup
  - Reverting workstation OU (if applied)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


4. Risk Assessment

Risk Level: Medium–High (specialised engineering software profiles)

Risks:
- CAD/scan tools may be tied to user SID
- Profile migration may corrupt user-specific paths
- Shared devices may cache licensing data under current user

Mitigations:
- Full profile backup prior to change
- Only test on isolated machine
- Run diff on `C:\ProgramData`, `HKLM\Software`, and `HKCU` post-logon
- Keep old profile untouched unless proven stable

SID-linked apps:
- Monitor SolidWorks registry
- Confirm MeshLab doesn't hardcode AppData


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


5. Rollback Procedure

1. Rename or delete new profile (e.g. `C:\Users\ModelShop-Test`)
2. Reassign old profile via regedit:
   - `HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\ProfileList`
3. Reapply shared account to workstation
4. Restore from:
   `\\fileserver\AuditBackups\ModelShop\{timestamp}\`

Confirm software integrity before full user migration.


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


6. Validation Criteria


✅ New user logs in with clean profile
✅ Software launches without config loss
✅ Scan devices detected
✅ Printers auto-mapped or manually installable
✅ Profile SID integrity preserved

If any fail:
❌ Rollback triggered


